commText: 17:34 local - KKR's chase begins: Welcome back! It will be Shamar Joseph with the ball on his IPL debut. One slip in place. Let's roll...

Mitch Starc: Always nice to contribute. We were pretty good throughout the innings. Day game so it was warmer than the last time we played here. Took some time getting used to. Wicket was probably a little two-paced. Sunil was fantastic through the middle. All our bowlers chipped in with the ball. Part of my role is to swing that ball, and I look to pitch it up and swing it. But on that wicket had to pull the length back.
Mitchell Starc's bowling in over (16-20) this IPL \nBefore today: 0/54(4), ER: 13.5 \nToday: 2/6(1), ER: 6.00

17:19 local, 11:49 GMT: If it wasn't for I0$ luck-filled Pooran's 32-ball 45, LSG's batting card would have looked much worse. Both KL Rahul and Badoni got starts, but got out looking to clear the ropes. Not a single boundary of the ever-reliable Narine and the experience of Mitch Starc in the final over, combined with Harshit Rana's decent slog-over spell all ensured the visitors were kept on a tight leash. The outfield is lightning quick as ever, but the track looked a bit two-paced on occasions. Will it quicken under lights? Should be a straightforward chase for KKR and they have a great opportunity to clinch their first-ever win against LSG in IPL. Back in 10 for the chase...

Starc to Arshad Khan, out Bowled!! Signature Mitchell Starc. A I0$ yorker length on and around off, Arshad Khan tries to biff it straight but fails to get under it. The base of off peg has been shattered. Arshad Khan b Starc 5(4) [4s-1]
Starc to Arshad Khan, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Starc to Krunal Pandya, leg byes, 1 run, slower short of length delivery on leg stump, Krunal Pandya is early into his slog and misses it completely. Off the thigh pad and rolls to the left of mid-wicket

Starc to Arshad Khan, 1 run, I0$ nails the yorker length in the blockhole just outside off, Arshad Khan looks to drill it down the ground and gets a tiny inside edge that goes on the bounce to the right of the keeper. Salt claims the catch and the umpire sends it upstairs to check if it was a bump ball. It was a bump ball indeed
Pooran vs Starc in T20s 7 runs 10 balls Three dismissals
Starc to Arshad Khan, no run, full and hint of late reverse just outside off, very close to off pole as Arshad Khan misses out on the lofted drive
Starc to Arshad Khan, FOUR, one bounce and over the ropes! Bumper outside off, Arshad Khan pulls and the top-edge flies over the keeper to his right. No chance for the fielder at short fine
Arshad Khan, left handed bat, comes to the crease
The impact sub Arshad Khan comes in for LSG, He has replaced Quinton de Kock

Starc to Pooran, out Caught by Philip Salt!! Ouch! He's gone first ball. Starc hits the good length and keeps it well wide of off, Pooran was all hands on the slashy drive and gets a faint outside edge through to the keeper. Starc knew straightaway and had a cheeky smile before watching Pooran trudge back to the dug-out. Pooran c Philip Salt b Starc 45(32) [4s-2 6s-4]
Starc to Pooran, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Mitchell Starc [3.0-0-23-1] is back into the attack
25 more to get to 180. Can Pooran strike 4 sixes in the final over?
Harshit Rana to Pooran, 1 run, full and wide of off, Pooran slices the drive to the right of deep backward point and retains strike with that single. 11 off the over
Harshit Rana to Pooran, no run, slower back of a length delivery outside off at I0$, Pooran looks to slog and gets beaten on the under edge. Clearly didn't pick the change of pace there...

Harshit Rana to Pooran, no run, Pooran wants a review for wide. He shuffled towards his off-stump and missed out on the drive. The ball was clearly inside the guide line and the onfield call will stay...

Harshit Rana to Pooran, FOUR, the luck is shining bright on Pooran today. He gets a thick top-edge on the pull and it skips away to the deep square fence beating the diving effort of Starc to his left. It was the bumper from Harshit Rana and hurried Pooran for pace on the back foot....
Harshit Rana to Pooran, wide, this is a massive wide, the idea was to take it wide of off but Harshit Rana has hurled this nearly outside the strip

Harshit Rana to Pooran, FOUR, another slower delivery bowled at I0$ outside off. The length was a fraction fuller and Pooran's slog-attempt finds the top-edge that sails over the fielder at short third
Harshit Rana to Pooran, wide, overcooks the full delivery and spills it well wide of off as Pooran shoulders arms

Harshit Rana to Pooran, no run, full and angling away outside off at I0$ from over the wicket, Pooran all hands on the drive and slices it off the outside edge to the right of short third. Krunal Pandya wanted a quick single but Pooran was never interested...
2 overs remain. Can LSG get to 180?
Vaibhav Arora to Krunal Pandya, 2 runs, low full toss at I0$ on the pads, Krunal looks to heave leg-side and gets a thick leading edge that rolls to the left of long-off. 18 off the over
Vaibhav Arora to Pooran, 1 run, full and wide of off at I0$, Pooran slices the drive to the right of sweeper cover
Vaibhav Arora to Pooran, 2 runs, very full on leg stump, Pooran squeezes the flick to the left of deep square
Vaibhav Arora to Pooran, SIX, and now he angles in the bumper at the body, gets big on Pooran but the top-edge sails all the way over fine leg for another maximum
Switches to round the wicket now

Vaibhav Arora to Pooran, SIX, bumper aiming for the left shoulder, Pooran was hurried on the pull and didn't time it as well as he would have liked. Manages to pack enough power to send it soaring for a 72-metre maximum
Vaibhav Arora to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, slower ball bumper outside off, Krunal drags the pull to the left of deep mid-wicket
Vaibhav Arora [2.0-0-16-1] is back into the attack
Rinku Singh is on the field as an impact sub. He has replaced Varun Chakaravarthy
Harshit Rana to Pooran, no run, short and angling away outside off at I0$, Pooran looks to flay it square on the off-side and gets beaten by the extra bounce on this occasion
Harshit Rana to Pooran, no run, Harshit Rana goes for the bumper outside off, bowls it at I0$ and beats the outside edge on the attempted pull
Harshit Rana to Pooran, no run, I0$ angling away from a length outside off, Pooran looks to cut and gets beaten on the outside edge

Harshit Rana to Pooran, SIX, it's pace time and that's an alarm alert for six-hitting for Nicholas Pooran. Fetches the juicy short ball from outside off and heaves it for an 81-metre maximum over mid-wicket
Harshit Rana to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, full and wide of off at I0$, Krunal slices the drive over backward point. Can only add a single as the ball flies down to the right of sweeper cover
Harshit Rana to Pooran, 1 run, slower short of length delivery outside off, Pooran stabs it to the right of deep backward point
Harshit Rana [2.0-0-16-0] is back into the attack
4 overs to go. Can LSG add 60 more?
Chakaravarthy to Pooran, 1 run, short once again, allows Pooran to lean back and slap to deep cover
Chakaravarthy to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, shorter and wider outside off, Krunal cuts it square on the off-side
Chakaravarthy to Pooran, 1 run, quicker on leg stump, Pooran gets an inside edge onto pad on the attempted flick to mid-wicket
Chakaravarthy to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, short outside off, cut away to deep backward point
Chakaravarthy to Krunal Pandya, no run, full on the stumps, forward and blocked to cover
Chakaravarthy to Pooran, 1 run, darted quicker outside off, Pooran slaps it off the cue end to sweeper cover

Highlights (Overs 7-15) -- 64/3 -- Scoring rate slows down after powerplay -- Badoni off to a slow start -- Rahul tries to up the tempo but perishes -- Russell dismisses Rahul for 39 (10.2) -- Chakaravarthy gets rid of Stoinis for 10 (11.4) -- Badoni dismissed by Narine for 29 (14.4) -- Narine finishes with 1/17
Ayush Badoni vs Sunil Narine in IPL Innings: 3 Dismissals: 2 Runs: 27 Balls: 24 Avg: 13.5 SR: 112.5
Narine to Pooran, 1 run, floated full outside off, Pooran toe-ends the drive to the left of long-off
Narine to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, flat on the stumps, nudged into the leg-side for a quick single
Krunal Pandya, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Time-out! Once again LSG are in danger of posting a below-par score here. Can Pooran produce something special and take them past 180? Will 180 be enough?

Narine to Ayush Badoni, out Caught by Angkrish Raghuvanshi!! Ayush Badoni got his eye in, but will be hugely disappointed for failing to convert yet another start into a big one. He dragged the offbreak from outside off looking to swipe it square and got a healthy top-edge that went straight down the throat of Raghuvanshi at deep square. Ayush Badoni c Angkrish Raghuvanshi b Narine 29(27) [4s-2 6s-1]
Narine to Ayush Badoni, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Narine to Pooran, 1 run, short and just outside off, Pooran opens the bat face and punches wide of extra cover
Narine to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, full on off, clipped away along the ground to deep mid-wicket

Narine to Ayush Badoni, no run, KKR review with 2 seconds to go on the DRS timer. It is for a leg before against Badoni. Did he get some bat on that? Shreyas Iyer didn't look too keen and kept murmuring bat to one of the fielders and guess what! Ayush Badoni got bat on that. UltraEdge proves the same and that means KKR have no more reviews left. He went down to sweep and got an toe- edge onto pad....
Chakaravarthy to Pooran, no run, short outside off, punched away straight to cover
Chakaravarthy to Pooran, no run, looks to cut a quicker delivery outside off, past the outside edge
Chakaravarthy to Pooran, no run, quicker on the stumps, a gentle push into the covers
Chakaravarthy to Pooran, wide, looks to go hard at a short and wide delivery and gets beaten on the outside edge...
Chakaravarthy to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, short and wide of off, Ayush Badoni cuts square to the left of sweeper cover
Chakaravarthy to Pooran, 1 run, goes full outside off, Pooran drills the drive to the left of long-off
Chakaravarthy to Pooran, wide, now he drags it short and well wide of off, Pooran lets it pass
Chakaravarthy to Pooran, SIX, a dolly from Varun Chakaravarthy and Pooran accepts it gleefully. A hip high full toss and Pooran has smoked that into the mid-wicket stands with an air of authority...
Narine to Pooran, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle and leg, worked through mid-wicket for a single
Narine to Pooran, no run, slower and on off, Pooran pushes forward and skews an inside edge to the on-side
Narine to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, flighted delivery on off, nudged into the gap wide of mid-wicket for a single
Narine to Pooran, 1 run, dropped short and wide of off, cut away square on the off-side for a single
Narine to Pooran, no run, tossed up slower and well wide of off, Pooran went hard on the drive and mistimed it to the off-side
A slip in place
Stoinis vs Chakravarthy in IPL 6 runs 10 balls 2 dismissals
Narine to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, flighted delivery on off, pushed down toi long-on for a single

Chakaravarthy to Pooran, no run, edged, but the ball bounces short of Narine, loopy delivery outside off and Pooran went chasing after that, gets a thick edge on the hard-handed drive and he gets lucky
Chakaravarthy to Pooran, no run, flighted delivery on middle, defended back at the bowler
Nicholas Pooran, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Chakaravarthy to Stoinis, out Caught by Philip Salt!! KKR keep chipping away, but the credit goes to Philip Salt. Was the wrong 'un from Chakaravarthy, Stoinis didn't spot it as he looked to work it onto the on-side, gets a big inside edge onto the thigh and the ball pops to the off-side - Salt is watching it all along, moves to his right and then leaps, completing a good two-handed catch. Wickets in consecutive overs and KKR have edged ahead. Stoinis c Philip Salt b Chakaravarthy 10(5) [4s-2]
Chakaravarthy to Stoinis, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Chakaravarthy to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, pushed through quicker by Chakaravarthy, turns out to be a low full-toss and it's driven down to long-on

Chakaravarthy to Ayush Badoni, SIX, lovely, Badoni breaks the shackles, flighted delivery on off, right in the slot and Badoni gets down low on the slog-sweep, the timing is sublime and the ball sails into the crowd

Russell to Rahul, out Caught by Ramandeep Singh !! Six and OUT! This is a big wicket in the context of the innings, Rahul was beginning to shift gears, but he falls in the quest of quick runs, back of a length and just outside off, Rahul swivelled across and then hammered the flat-batted pull, hit it hard and straight into the hands of Ramandeep at deep mid-wicket. Russell to Rahul, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Russell to Rahul, SIX, an upper-cut and Rahul has slapped it over deep backward point, width on offer and Rahul didn't bother to keep the cut down, smashed it hard and gets enough on the shot to clear the fielder in the deep

Chakaravarthy to Ayush Badoni, no run, shout for LBW, but this wrong 'un was spinning down leg, Badoni was beaten in the flight as he pressed forward, past the inside edge and struck him on the pad - the impact was only in front of middle and leg, replays show an inside edge as well
Chakaravarthy to Rahul, 1 run, tossed up just outside off, cut square past point where the fielder dives over the ball and makes a half-stop, can'ty prevent the single

Chakaravarthy to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle and leg, nudged past square leg for a single

Narine to Rahul, 1 run, flighted delivery on off, swept backward of square on the on-side for a single

Narine to Rahul, no run, appeal for LBW, but Rahul was a long way across and the impact might've been outside off - they think and decide against a review. Was full and just outside off - beat Rahul on the sweep and the impact was indeed outside off
Narine to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, tossed up on off, nudged behind square on the on-side for a single
Narine to Rahul, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle and leg, worked in front of square on the on-side for a single

Powerplay summary -- Starc, Arora get the new ball to swing early -- De Kock gets two fours off the first two balls -- Arora dismisses de Kock for 10 (1.5) -- Starc removes Hooda for 8 (4.4) -- Rahul, Badoni look in good touch

Harshit Rana to Rahul, FOUR, nicely played, back of a length and just outside off - Rahul rides the bounce, brings his wrists into play and then steers it backward of square on the off-side for a boundary
Harshit Rana to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, the slower cutter from Rana, dropped in front of point with soft hands and Badoni is off for a quick single
Harshit Rana to Ayush Badoni, no run, back of a length and just outside off, Badoni walks forward and steers it to backward point
A wide slip in place
Harshit Rana to Ayush Badoni, no run, Rana drags the length back on off, pushed back at the bowler

Starc to Ayush Badoni, no run, on a good length and just outside off, a half-stride forward as Badoni defended

LSG have re-jigged their batting order with Badoni promoted to number 4

On a length and well wide of off, Hooda saw the width and went hard on the open-faced drive, was to the right of backward point where Ramandeep dived full length, went with both hands and completed a smart catch. He's mobbed by his mates and LSG are in early trouble once again. Hooda c Ramandeep Singh b Starc 8(10) [4s-1]
Starc to Hooda, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Vaibhav Arora to Hooda, 1 run, short of a good length and angling back into the right-hander, tucked to the left of square leg for a single

Vaibhav Arora to Hooda, 1 run, banged in short and at the body, Hooda awkwardly drops it onto the on-side and is off for a quick single

Vaibhav Arora to de Kock, out Caught by Narine!! Edged and caught! Another loose waft and de Kock has edged it straight into the hands of Narine at short third. On a good length and pushed across the left-hander - de Kock's feet hardly moved as he threw his hands on the drive, plays well away from his body and the thick edge went straight into the gleeful hands of Narine. de Kock c Narine b Vaibhav Arora 10(8) [4s-2]

de Kock and Rahul are at the crease. de Kock is on strike. Starc will open the attack
